<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 25 at 4:28AM CDT  by NWS Dodge City</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHEASTERN FORD...SOUTHEASTERN
HODGEMAN AND SOUTHWESTERN EDWARDS COUNTIES THROUGH 500 AM CDT...
At 428 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spearville, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Spearville and Windhorst around 435 AM CDT.
Bellefont around 440 AM CDT.
Offerle around 445 AM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
